css=it is stand for cascading style sheet
it is used to give  a stylish look to the web site or web page


# how to add a css

there are three ways to add a css
1) inline style-adding a style directly to the each element 

exp- <h1 style="color: red; background-color:blue">web development</h1>

2) using <style> </style>tag-  adding a css by using style tag in a same document

exp- <style>
             h1{
                color:red
                background-color:black
             }
       
    </style>

3) external-stylesheet- writing a css in separate file and linking it with html document by using link tag

exp-  <link rel="stylesheet"  href="style.css">

here we using a two attribute in link tag

rel-this specify the relation .i.e what type of sheet we are going to link
href-it specify the source path of css

note-link tag should be in head tad